					<p>
					The <b>Best Pharmacy college of Punjab</b> (CGC- Landran) provides the M. Pharmacy (M.Pharm) course in Pharmaceutics, Pharmacology, Pharmaceutical chemistry and Quality Assurance include a 4 semester course work. M.Pharmacy in Pharmaceutics includes mechanisms of drug action, advances in pharmacology and clinical management of diseases is covered.<br/>
					In Pharmacology, students undertake one year dissertation work in the second year of their degree on analytical techniques and methodologies. M.Pharmacy in Pharmaceutical chemistry provides students the significant knowledge of chemistry required in the drug development and spectral technique for drug analysis etc. <br/>
					
					<ul class='listing'>
   						<li>M.Pharmacy in Quality Assurance provides students the relevant knowledge about the techniques used to ensure the quality of product and various procedures for testing the drug product or drug substance to prepare the various protocols like SOP, STP validation procedure.</li>
   						<li>Students study the novel drug delivery systems, design of dosage form and pharmacokinetic study of drug in M.Pharmacy.</li><br/>
   					</ul>
					
					<span>Advantages and Future Career Prospects of M.Pharm</span><br/><br/>
 					Indian pharmaceutical enterprises are in the top rank of India's science based industries, especially in multifaceted fields like Technology and Drug manufacturing. Pharmaceutical industry is growing at about 8 to 9% annually and is likely to be worth over Rs 20000 crores in the coming years.<br/><br/>
 					
 					<span>Eligibility Criteria</span><br/><br/> 
					In order to get admission in the CGC-Top Pharmacy College in Punjab then a candidate must have a bachelor's degree in B-Pharmacy with minimum 55% marks in qualifying degree.<br/><br/>
 
					<span>Admission Procedure</span><br/><br/> 
					33% of the total seats are made directly by the college on the basis of merit of the qualifying exam. 
